1️⃣ LOGICAL REASONING – PUZZLES (ADVANCED + SHORTCUTS)

This is top-level placement difficulty
(Asked in TCS, Infosys, Accenture, etc.)

🔹 A. COMMON ADVANCED TYPES

1️⃣ Linear + Conditions
2️⃣ Circular + Facing direction
3️⃣ Multiple variables (name + profession + place)
4️⃣ Ranking puzzles

🔹 B. KEY STRATEGY (VERY IMPORTANT)

👉 Always follow:

Read all conditions once
Find direct placements
Fix positions
Fill remaining logically
🔹 C. EXAMPLE (ADVANCED)

5 people: A, B, C, D, E

Conditions:

A is left of B
C is right of B
D is not at ends
E is at one end
Step 1: Fix E at one end

E _ _ _ _

Step 2: D not at ends

E _ D _ _

Step 3: A left of B, C right of B

Try placements:

Final possible arrangement:

E A B C D

🔹 D. IMPORTANT SHORTCUTS

1️⃣ Fix extreme positions first
2️⃣ Use elimination method
3️⃣ Convert words → symbols
4️⃣ Avoid rewriting full names

🔹 E. RANKING TYPE
Example

A is taller than B
B taller than C

👉 Order:

A > B > C

🔹 F. MULTI-VARIABLE PUZZLES

Example:

A is doctor
B is engineer
C is teacher

👉 Solve one variable at a time

📝 PRACTICE QUESTIONS
5 people sit in row, A left of B, C right of B. Who is in middle?
A > B > C > D. Who is smallest?
In circle, A sits opposite B. How many people minimum?
A not at ends, B at left end. Where can C sit?
4 people with jobs (doctor, teacher, engineer, lawyer). Match logically.
